  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate periodontal and systemic parameters of a cohort of chronic kidney
      disease (stage 5) patients, before and three months after non-surgical periodontal treatment.
      It does not consider a control group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Dental biofilm is a source of inflammation and infection of periodontal tissues. In the last
      20 years the interaction between periodontal infections and systemic conditions has been
      largely studied, suggesting that the inflammation caused in the periodontal tissues could
      cause a response in other parts of the body.

      Recent studies suggest that there could be an association between periodontal disease and
      chronic kidney disease.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
